_json.gridTitle: Bianco Avorio Cardoon Plant | Cynara cardunculus
_json.description: Cardoon Plant Bianco Avorio A vegetable widely cultivated in Victorian England that is related to the Globe Artichoke - except it's the stems that are cooked and used in late Autumn/Winter rather than the flowerheads.  We grow and eat this ourselves and you may recall it was featured by Harry Dodson in the BBC Victorian Kitchen Garden series.
